<subSubSection id="C33D2F9B991DFFA2FF79537B6063ED33" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B987C10991DFFA2FF79537B6063ED33" blockId="4.[151,1437,942,1975]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B953A002991DFFA2FF79537B6343ED17" bold="true" box="[199,334,1843,1867]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin &quot; 
<emphasis id="B953A002991DFFA2FCF3537C6180ED17" box="[845,909,1844,1867]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">minut</emphasis>
&quot;, corresponding to the smaller size of the adult compared with other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D2F9B991DFFA2FF795333678EEDEA" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B987C10991DFFA2FF795333678EEDEA" blockId="4.[151,1437,942,1975]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B953A002991DFFA2FF7953336336EDCF" bold="true" box="[199,315,1915,1939]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="549CC2B2991DFFA2FEC4533263D1EDCE" box="[378,476,1914,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
is partly destroyed. However, the external characters are obviously distinguishable from other species of the genus by the longer and stronger white stripe on ventral margin of cell of the forewing.
</paragraph>
